      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary52.jpg"/>
            <dateline>Friday 28.</dateline>
            <p>This was a bright fine day - a languid summer day. Part of the Regiment moved
               to our new camp nearer to town, but still on this side of the Trent, near to
               where we bivouaced the first night. I was officer of the day, though I was so
               horase that I could not speak above my breath. Toward evening I think my cold
               is broken up some.</p>
         </div>
